node.title: Police name man who died in Taupō motel
node.description: The man whose death is being investigated after he died at a motel in Taupō last Sunday has been named.
node.content:
["The man whose death is being investigated after he died at a motel in Taup\u014d last Sunday has been named.", "", "
\nPhoto: Google Maps\n
", "He was 30-year-old Ryan Whare Woodford from Taup\u014d.", "The acting area manager, investigations, of Taup\u014d CIB, Detective Sergeant Andy Livingstone said an autopsy was completed today in Auckland.", "Police are continuing to investigate Woodford's death in an inquiry being referred to as Operation Dell.", "The homicide inquiry was launched just after 6.30am on Sunday after Woodford died at the Adelphi Motel on the corner of Kaimanawa Street and Heuheu Street.", "Livingstone praised the efforts of other motel residents who came to Woodford's aid and also alerted emergency services.", "He said police are also receiving community support as detectives try and piece together what happened.", "Anyone who has information can call 105 and quote Operation Dell, Taup\u014d.", "Information can also be provided anonymously to Crime Stoppers on 0800 555 111."]
